From: Harald Freudenberger <freude@linux.ibm.com>
Subject: kernel: Add CEX7 toleration support
Patch-mainline: never, SLES 11 SP4 only
References: bsc#1131295 LTC#176628

Summary:     kernel: Add CEX7 toleration support
Description: Add toleration support for new CEX7 crypto card
             Please note: The upstream solution for handling
             new crypto cards is done via the QACT instruction.
             See upstream id 9a5641080bf433e195730e47a13de58dcd70f47f.

Signed-off-by: Harald Freudenberger <freude@linux.ibm.com>
Acked-by: Petr Tesarik <ptesarik@suse.com>
---
 drivers/s390/crypto/ap_bus.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/s390/crypto/ap_bus.c
+++ b/drivers/s390/crypto/ap_bus.c
@@ -1505,6 +1505,7 @@ static void ap_scan_bus(struct work_stru
 			break;
 		case 11:
 		case 12:
+		case 13:
 			ap_dev->device_type = 10;
 			break;
 		default:
